2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 87
BY REPRESENTATIVE DEVILLIER
A RESOLUTION
To express the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death of Roger D.
Boudreaux.
WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the passing, on March 28,
2026, of Roger D. Boudreaux; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Boudreaux served as mayor of Church Point, Louisiana, for sixteen
years and was an energetic supporter of the town, its schools, and the local Filipino
community; he also cherished following his descendants' sports competitions; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Boudreaux was a member of the Bears Booster Club for over thirty
years; he was a founder and twenty-two-year member of Cajun Woodstock; and
WHEREAS, Roger D. Boudreaux is survived by his wife, Seina Campos Boudreaux;
daughter, Stephanie Aguillard; sons, Nathan Boudreaux (Lisa) and Blake Boudreaux (Skie);
"bonus" daughter, Mia Dominguez (Jesus); grandchildren, Drake Boudreaux, Hannah
Boudreaux, Gabrielle Boudreaux, Josh Boudreaux, Caiden Boudreaux, Landon Boudreaux,
Bentley Boudreaux, Liam Boudreaux, Dylan Stelly, Destiny Stelly, and Slade Stelly; and
"bonus" grandchildren, Haven Dominguez, Dontae Dominguez, Izaiah Dominguez, and
Andria Dominguez; he will be deeply missed, but the legacy of his love and service to the
town of Church Point shall live on in the hearts and minds of those who were privileged to
have known and loved him.
